From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Andrei Aldea <andrei1998@gmail.com>
Date: Wed, 22 Jul 2026 17:05:00 -0500
Subject: [PATCH] remoteproc: ti: k3: support 48-bit DMA addresses

The J722S EdgeAI memory map places the shared DMA-BUF carveout above the
32-bit address boundary.  Restore the TI vendor-kernel setup that gives K3
DSP and R5 remoteproc devices a 48-bit DMA mask, otherwise DMA-BUF mapping
falls back to SWIOTLB and large TIDL allocations fail.

Signed-off-by: Andrei Aldea <andrei1998@gmail.com>
---
 drivers/remoteproc/ti_k3_dsp_remoteproc.c | 5 +++++
 drivers/remoteproc/ti_k3_r5_remoteproc.c  | 4 ++++
 2 files changed, 9 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/remoteproc/ti_k3_dsp_remoteproc.c b/drivers/remoteproc/ti_k3_dsp_remoteproc.c
index 3223558db..d091a2b07 100644
--- a/drivers/remoteproc/ti_k3_dsp_remoteproc.c
+++ b/drivers/remoteproc/ti_k3_dsp_remoteproc.c
@@ -6,6 +6,7 @@
  *	Suman Anna <s-anna@ti.com>
  */
 
+#include <linux/dma-mapping.h>
 #include <linux/io.h>
 #include <linux/mailbox_client.h>
 #include <linux/module.h>
@@ -154,6 +155,10 @@ static int k3_dsp_rproc_probe(struct platform_device *pdev)
 		dev_info(dev, "configured DSP for remoteproc mode\n");
 	}
 
+	ret = dma_coerce_mask_and_coherent(&rproc->dev, DMA_BIT_MASK(48));
+	if (ret)
+		dev_warn(dev, "failed to set 48-bit DMA mask (%d)\n", ret);
+
 	ret = devm_rproc_add(dev, rproc);
 	if (ret)
 		return dev_err_probe(dev, ret, "failed to add register device with remoteproc core\n");
diff --git a/drivers/remoteproc/ti_k3_r5_remoteproc.c b/drivers/remoteproc/ti_k3_r5_remoteproc.c
index d492026fc..b50d2fb44 100644
--- a/drivers/remoteproc/ti_k3_r5_remoteproc.c
+++ b/drivers/remoteproc/ti_k3_r5_remoteproc.c
@@ -1047,6 +1047,10 @@ static int k3_r5_cluster_rproc_init(struct platform_device *pdev)
 			goto out;
 		}
 
+		ret = dma_coerce_mask_and_coherent(&rproc->dev, DMA_BIT_MASK(48));
+		if (ret)
+			dev_warn(dev, "failed to set 48-bit DMA mask (%d)\n", ret);
+
 		/* K3 R5s have a Region Address Translator (RAT) but no MMU */
 		rproc->has_iommu = false;
 		/* error recovery is not supported at present */
-- 
2.50.1
